Leo X forms an alliance with the newly elected Holy Roman Emperor Charles V against France. This alliance helps the Papal States increase in territory after French forces are defeated. However, Leo's lavish spending contributes to the poor financial state of the Papacy. He dies in 1521 with the Papal States larger but the Papacy deeply in debt.
